The paper presents a new model-based algorithm for reinforcement learning (RL) that is applicable in large or infinite state spaces. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The algorithm also involves exploration and exploitation phases, which are common in Robotics (cs.RO) and Control Systems (cs.SY) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks, which are commonly used in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.DS.
